        "content": "<p>I am not sure you have the right statement yet. Instead, it should probably be : if <code>X</code> is a real-valued random variable, <code>Y</code> is vector-valued, and both are integrable and independent, then <code>X â€¢ Y</code> is integrable and <code>E (X â€¢ Y) = E X â€¢ E Y</code>. Or, even better: if <code>B</code> is bilinear continuous and <code>X</code> and <code>Y</code> are independent, then <code>E (B X Y) = B (E X) (E Y)</code>(is that even true? :-)</p>",
